#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:5
msgid "Audio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:7
msgid ""
"Emscripten ships with its own implementation of the OpenAL 1.1 API, using "
"the Web Audio API as a backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:9
msgid ""
"You can reasonably expect ported OpenAL applications to \"just work\" with "
"no additional effort. Just link with the ``-lopenal`` linker flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:11
msgid ""
"There are some implementation-specific aspects which are worth considering "
"and are documented here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:13
msgid ""
"There used to be no additional flag to pass to the compiler in order to use "
"OpenAL. However, specifying ``-lopenal`` as mentioned above should be "
"considered mandatory (at some point in the future, it **will** be)!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:19
msgid "Supported OpenAL extensions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:21
msgid ""
"The following extensions are supported by Emscripten's OpenAL implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:23
msgid "``ALC_SOFT_pause_device``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:24
msgid "``ALC_SOFT_HRTF``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:25
msgid "``AL_EXT_float32``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:26
msgid "``AL_SOFT_loop_points``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:27
msgid "``AL_SOFT_source_length``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:28
msgid "``AL_EXT_source_distance_model``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:29
msgid "``AL_SOFT_source_spatialize``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:31
msgid ""
"This doesn't mean you should just assume their presence ! For correctness, "
"you should **always** check if an extension is supported before using it, "
"like a good application would do."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:37
msgid "Guidelines for Audio on Emscripten"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:39
msgid ""
"Know that your application needs to yield to the Javascript main loop for "
"audio processing to take place (See :ref:`Browser main loop <emscripten-"
"runtime-environment-main-loop>`). Put simply, this kind of code will block "
"indefinitely:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:49
msgid ""
"The above snippet usually works in native applications because most OpenAL "
"implementations own and manage one or more separate threads. This is **not** "
"the case in Emscripten. What you must do instead is perform each such query "
"only once per \"main loop iteration\" (i.e the callback you provide via :c:"
"func:`emscripten_set_main_loop` or :c:func:`emscripten_set_main_loop_arg`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:55
msgid ""
"Another issue you may experience is that browsers will not allow audio to "
"play before user input. This prevents pages from auto-playing media, which "
"can be annoying if you didn't want that. Emscripten's OpenAL implementation "
"(and also SDL1) will automatically listen for a user click or keypress on "
"the document and the canvas, and resume audio for you. That means that audio "
"should start to play once the user does something on the page. (See "
"``autoResumeAudioContext()`` for how this is done internally.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:66
msgid "Emscripten-specific capture behavior"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:68
msgid ""
"Attempting to open an input stream to the user's audio capture device "
"results in the asynchronous appearance of a small browser-specific dialog "
"asking for the user's permission, and on some browsers, the capture device "
"to choose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:73
msgid ""
"With this in mind, when ``alcCaptureOpenDevice()`` is called with valid and "
"supported parameters, a \"proxy\" device is returned, which successfully "
"captures no sample until the user clicks \"Allow\" on said dialog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:77
msgid ""
"That means, when calling ``alcGetIntegerv(device, ALC_CAPTURE_SAMPLES, 1, "
"&nframes)``, ``nframes`` remains set to zero until the user clicks "
"\"Allow\". You might want to make your app handle this specific behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:79
msgid ""
"If the user clicks \"Deny\", the device is invalidated (because this is "
"somewhat similar to unplugging the physical device) and calls to "
"``alcCapture*`` functions on that device then consistently fail with "
"``ALC_INVALID_DEVICE``. Your application should be prepared to handle this "
"properly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:85
msgid ""
"Some browsers \"remember\" this choice and apply it automatically every time "
"it would be asked again instead. There's no way for the implementation to "
"detect this behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:92
msgid "Useful implementation details of OpenAL capture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:94
msgid ""
"Internally, Web Audio's capture data is always backed by a Javascript "
"``Float32Array``. Thus, ``AL_FORMAT_MONO_FLOAT32`` and "
"``AL_FORMAT_STEREO_FLOAT32`` are the only formats which do not require "
"converting acquired samples from their initial type to another."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:97
msgid ""
"Also, the actual sample rate at which samples are acquired from the device "
"is currently dictated by the browser and hardware, instead of user code. If "
"this sample rate does not match the one your app requests, the "
"implementation is required to perform resampling on your behalf."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:99
msgid ""
"That sample rate is given by ``audioCtx.sampleRate``, where ``audioCtx`` is "
"the ``AudioContext`` object used internally by the relevant capture "
"``ALCdevice``. Currently, Emscripten provides no direct way for applications "
"to access this value, but this might be provided through an Emscripten-"
"specific OpenAL extension (which is not here yet because it requires "
"registration)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:102
msgid ""
"Right now though there's a quick and *de facto* reliable way to do this (C "
"example):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:122
msgid ""
"It is reasonable to expect this sample rate to be either 44100Hz or 48000Hz. "
"You can test it right now by copying the javascript part into your browser's "
"console if you're curious."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:128
msgid "Improving and extending the implementation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:130
msgid ""
"Currently, the OpenAL capture implementation performs naïve linear "
"resampling because it is simple and the small loss of quality was deemed "
"acceptable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:132
msgid ""
"However, you're welcome to improve this by contributing if you so wish! See "
"`this issue <https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/issues/5349>`_ , "
"for instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/Audio.rst:134
msgid ""
"Likewise, if you'd like to see a particular extension implemented (whether "
"it is registered or not), then your best bet is to either file an issue "
"(provided no related prior issue existed for this), or contribute! See :ref:"
"`Contributing <contributing>` for guidelines."
msgstr ""
